data.title: Obituary for Dorothy A. O'Donovan

data.meta_site_name: Obituary for Dorothy A. O'Donovan | Barnegat Funeral Home
data.text:
Dorothy A. O'Donovan, 74, of Barnegat passed on Saturday, September 15, 2018. Born in the Bronx, NY to her late parents, William and Dorothy Wyrick, she formerly resided in Bayonne, NJ and was a member of the Meat Wrappers Union, having worked at Pathmark in Jersey City.

Predeceased by her sister, Louise Wyrick, and her brother, William Wyreck, she is survived by her beloved husband of 55 years, James O'Donovan; her loving son, Michael and his wife Colleen O'Donovan; three cherished grandchildren, Faith, Shannon and Liam.

Viewing Tuesday, September 18, 2018 from 2 to 4 and 7 to 9 PM at Barnegat Funeral Home, 841 West Bay Ave., Barnegat. Mass offered Wednesday 11 AM at St. Mary's Church, Barnegat. Entombment to follow in Ocean County Memorial Park, Waretown.
